					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">Sik wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">You can remove a few tiles at the sides (they will not be visible anyway due to overscan)</div><br />Side tiles are very visible on every recent TV that I've used. True, the official background planning sheets used 224x192 (which corresponds to 10% border per side), but modern video standards are closer to 3-5% border per side. The 4:3 frame in NTSC is 280x240 NES pixels in size, and a (280 - 256)/2 = 12 pixel border on the left and right sides is 4.2%.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

